        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Monitoring"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 43
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.1,
                "text": "Due to a wide variability in the handling of vancomycin, early analysis of a vancomycin concentration is required to ensure the dosage regimen is appropriate."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 44
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Take a serum sample level within 12-24hours of starting the continuous infusion, then daily at 06.00hrs or thereabout."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 45
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.0,
                "text": "Based on the level result, the daily dose and rate may need to be adjusted according to Table  by the medical staff. Ward based pharmacist should always check the accuracy of vancomycin continuous infusion prescription whenever they are on the ward."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 46
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Target steady state concentration range: 15 \u2013 25 mg/L"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 47
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.2,
                "text": "In severe and/or deep-seated infections, aim for a higher target of 20-25mg/L."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 48
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 5.3,
                "text": "If the patient is failing to respond, seek advice from microbiology or an infection specialist."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 49
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 5.4,
                "text": "Patients on continuous hemofiltration: Once dialysis is discontinued, and if vancomycin is still required, vancomycin levels should be taken within 4- 6 hours after hemofiltration ends. This allows adequate time to monitor the patient's handling of the drug post filtration. The new maintenance dose should be based on the post-hemofiltration plasma vancomycin level."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 50
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "prefix": 6.0,
                "text": "Interpretation of Vancomycin level"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 51
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.1,
                "text": "Always check the dosage history and sampling time are appropriate before interpreting the result."
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 52
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "prefix": 6.2,
                "text": "If the measured level is unexpectedly high or low consider the following:"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 53
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Was the right dose administered?"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 54
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Was the sample time recorded accurately?"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 55
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Was the sample taken from the line used to administer the drug?"
            },
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 56
        },
        {
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Has the renal function declined or improved?"
